1&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11864,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/29\/speechh-haqq-silence-safe\/","url_meta":{"origin":41396,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Silence: Speak truth, or be silent and safe","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 29, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cMay Allah have mercy on a man who spoke rightly and was rewarded, or who was silent and remained safe.\u201d Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n 4589 Grade:\u00a0Hasan\u00a0(fair) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25100,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/07\/23\/ibn-sireen-biggest-sinners\/","url_meta":{"origin":41396,"position":2},"title":"Ibn Sirin on Sin: Biggest sinners mention other people\u2019s sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 23, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Hisham ibn Hassan reported: Muhammad ibn Sirin, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cWe used to say that people with the most faults are the quickest of them to mention the faults of others.\u201d Source: al-S\u0323amt li Ibn Abi\u0304 Dunya\u0304 138 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0647\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0627\